nobody2007:

"Delta" is NOT a version or build stability indication. It is just a word for the update that can be used to update previous systems

There's "Combo" and "Delta" versions of the update. One to update all previous versions and one only to update the last one.

Where Delta is the one that can only be used to update the last version (in this case 10.4.8) and Combo is the one that have the combined updates for all previous systems of that generation (10.4.x -> 10.4.9)

Not to say that this isn't a Beta or Developer release (which it is), but don't get Delta confused with Alpha/Beta material as it isn't  an indicator of the code stability as those other two are.

10.4.9 seems to be on-hold from apple, it's been nearly 5 months since the last update. This is one of the longest times ever for a OS X system update to come. Apple is waiting for something else to release this update (or maybe they are just holding off to get a last, really stable, release of tiger on the streets)
